eturn</span> s.trim().split(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;[\\\\s]+&quot;</span>).length;\n  }\n\n  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">/**\n   * counts the number of words in a sentence but ignores all potential non-alphanumeric characters\n   * that do not represent a word. runs in O(n) where n is the length of s\n   *\n   * <span class=\"hljs-doctag\">@param</span> s String: sentence with word(s)\n   * <span class=\"hljs-doctag\">@return</span> int: number of words\n   */</span>\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\">int</span> <span class=\"hljs-title function_\">secondaryWordCount</span><span class=\"hljs-params\">(String s)</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">if</span> (s == <span class=\"hljs-literal\">null</span> || s.isEmpty()) <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-number\">0</span>;\n    <span class=\"hljs-type\">StringBuilder</span> <span class=\"hljs-variable\">sb</span> <span class=\"hljs-operator\">=</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-title class_\">StringBuilder</span>();\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">for</span> (<span class=\"hljs-type\">char</span> c : s.toCharArray()) {\n      <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">if</span> (Character.isLetter(c) || Character.isDigit(c)) sb.append(c);\n    }\n    s = sb.toString();\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">return</span> s.trim().split(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;[\\\\s]+&quot;</span>).length;\n  }\n}\n"
